ProtoResult:
. "Let $p(x) = x^n + a_{n-1} x^{n-1} + \cdots + a_0$ be a 
   polynomial with coefficients in ${\mathbb Z}$ and $a_0 \neq 
   0$. If $p(x)$ has a zero in ${\mathbb Q}$, then $p(x)$ also 
   has a zero $\alpha$ in ${\mathbb Z}$. Furthermore, $\alpha$ 
   divides $a_0$."
